    <note type="biography">
        <p>Expressman. In 1844, became messenger for Wells &amp; Company, of which he was one of three owners. Secretary of the American Express Company in 1850. Wells, Fargo &amp; Company established the first express to and from California in 1852. President of the American Merchants Union Express Company, 1868. Mayor of Buffalo, New York, 1862–6.</p></note>
